<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Robe" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Robe,</orth> any garment: <cit><quote>in these unreverent --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 114</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that lion's r.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 141</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 141</bibl> <cit><quote>is not a buff jerkin a most sweet r. of durance?</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>our easy --s of peace,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 12</bibl></cit>. <emph>they</emph> (our soldiers) <cit><quote>will be in fresher --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 117</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a child that hath new --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>lest our old --s sit easier than our new,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.4.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 4, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>like a giant's robe upon a dwarfish thief,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when old --s are worn out,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 171</bibl></cit><lb />== a splendid female gown: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 4, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 3.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.134" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.217" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 217</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.530" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 530</bibl>.
<lb />== a gown of state, a dress of dignity: <bibl n="shak. son 52.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 52, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.37" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.279" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 279</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.453" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 453</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 2, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.283" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 224</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>